1 Section 11-1304. A. The Department of Public Safety is
2 authorized to establish Operation Work Zone Awareness. Operation
3 Work Zone Awareness is a program designed to educate the motoring
4 public on the dangers of committing moving violations while
5 traveling in highway construction work zones or motorists failing to
6 move over or slow down pursuant to subsection D of Section 11-314 of
7 this title. The Department is authorized to develop and house on
8 its website an online work zone awareness presentation that may
9 include, but not be limited to, facts and figures representing the
10 dangers of motorists committing work zone moving violations,
11 testimonials from highway construction workers and their families,
12 information on the importance of awareness and slowing down in work
13 zones, the importance of moving over or slowing down, and a
14 question-and-answer section to ensure participants understand and
15 retain the information presented. The Department is authorized to
16 contract for the production, development, and maintenance of the
17 webpage through a vendor. The Department shall maintain in its
18 database a record of those completing the program.
19 B. Motorists receiving a citation for committing moving
20 violations within a work zone or for failure to move over or slow
21 down may receive information regarding an invitation to participate
22 in the Operation Work Zone Awareness program. A motorist who
23 participates in and completes the online program shall receive a
24 certificate designed and issued by the Department. Any person
Req. No. 10281 Page 5

1 prod ucing the certificate as proof in court that the program was
2 successfully completed shall be entitled to dismissal of the fine.
3 If proof of successful completion of the program is presented to the
4 court in person or electronically, no later than the business day
5 preceding the first scheduled court appearance date, the dismissal
6 shall be without payment of court costs. The court may access
7 information from the Department’s system to confirm completion of
8 the program. Offenders may participate in and complete the program
9 a maximum of one time. After completing the program, a motorist who
10 receives another citation in a work zone or for failure to move over
11 or slow down will be disqualified from utilizing the program
12 benefits a second time. If a motorist so chooses, he or she may not
13 participate in the program and instead pay the fine imposed on the
14 issued citation. Holders of commercial driver licenses cited while
15 driving a commercial motor vehicle are not eligible to participate
16 in the program.
17 C. Moving violations that qualify an offender to participate in
18 the Operation Work Zone Awareness program shall include, but not be
19 limited to, speeding, distracted driving, failure to move over,
20 failure to obey flagger, and failure to obey traffic control
21 devices. Motorists committing impaired driving offenses, as defined
22 in Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes, in work zones or otherwise,
23 including driving under the influence, driving while intoxicated,
24 driving under the influence under twenty-one (21) years of age, or a
Req. No. 10281 Page 6

1 comm ercial driver license holder refusing a chemical test while
2 driving any vehicle, shall be disqualified from the program.
3 D. The fee paid by a motorist for his or her participation in
4 the Operation Work Zone Awareness program shall be Seventy-five
5 Dollars ($75.00) and shall be apportioned as follows:
6 1. Thirty-five Dollars ($35.00) to be deposited in the
7 Department of Public Safety Revolving Fund, created in Section 2-
8 144.1 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes, to be used for
9 maintenance of the Operation Work Zone Awareness program;
10 2. Fifteen Dollars ($15.00) to be deposited in the Department
11 of Public Safety Patrol Vehicle Revolving Fund, created in Section
12 2-143 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes; and
13 3. Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00) to be deposited in the Oklahoma
14 Court Information System Revolving Fund, created in Section 1315 of
15 Title 20 of the Oklahoma Statutes, to be used to offset expenses
16 related to this program.
17 The Department is authorized to determine the manner in which
18 fees may be paid.
19 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
